@PombeirP right, it tries to start it again here https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/develop/src/status_im/ui/screens/accounts/login/events.cljs#L121
if node was not started, i.e. `node.started` signal has not been received which is the case in this TF session https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8473772/sessions/4393840579/?accessToken=KfcXCyz8skvcYe8vtXbR7hwc/rA) Signal `node.started` only received on `00:10`, but not between 6s and 9s where first `StartNode` was called.

<blockquote><div><strong><a href="https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8473772/sessions/4393840579/?accessToken=KfcXCyz8skvcYe8vtXbR7hwc/rA">TestFairy: Status 0.9.19 (6044) @2018</a></strong></div></blockquote>

@mandrigin `update-token-balance-fail` seems not related as it tells about token balance update failure only.
We update ETH balance with `update-balance` that have `update-balance-success` and `update-balance-fail` callback events. https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/develop/src/status_im/ui/screens/wallet/events.cljs#L123

